PROMPT data_catalog_explanation
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a data governance expert specializing in metadata management, data catalogs, and enterprise data discovery platforms with deep knowledge of leading data catalog tools and their metadata capabilities.")

GENERATE
    explain_data_catalog("Explain what a data catalog is and provide detailed information about two specific tools, covering: the definition of a data catalog as a centralized repository that organizes and manages metadata about an organization's data assets, providing a searchable inventory of datasets, tables, columns, and their relationships to enable data discovery, understanding, and governance across the enterprise, the core functions including data discovery through search and browse capabilities, data lineage tracking to show data origins and transformations, data quality monitoring and profiling, access control and security management, and collaboration features for data stewardship, two specific data catalog tools: Apache Atlas as an open-source metadata management and data governance framework originally developed by Hortonworks, now part of the Apache Software Foundation, designed for Hadoop ecosystems but extensible to other platforms, storing technical metadata including table schemas, column definitions, data types, partitioning information, and storage locations, business metadata such as data owner information, business glossary terms, data classifications, and usage policies, operational metadata covering data lineage from source to consumption, job execution history, data quality metrics, and access patterns, relationship metadata that maps dependencies between datasets, transformations, and downstream consumers, and security metadata including access permissions, data sensitivity classifications, and compliance tags, versus Collibra as a leading commercial data governance platform that provides comprehensive data catalog functionality with enterprise-grade features, storing similar technical metadata including database schemas, API specifications, file structures, and system integrations, extensive business metadata capabilities such as business glossary management, data stewardship workflows, policy definitions, and stakeholder assignments, advanced lineage metadata that automatically discovers and visualizes end-to-end data flows across complex enterprise environments, data quality metadata including profiling results, quality rules, issue tracking, and remediation workflows, governance metadata covering compliance frameworks, regulatory requirements, data retention policies, and audit trails, collaboration metadata that tracks user interactions, comments, ratings, and data usage analytics, the key differences between these tools including Apache Atlas being open-source and primarily focused on Hadoop ecosystems with strong technical lineage capabilities, while Collibra is a commercial platform offering broader enterprise features, advanced workflow capabilities, and comprehensive business user interfaces, how both tools integrate with various data sources, ETL tools, and analytics platforms to automatically capture and maintain metadata, and the benefits each provides for data teams including improved data discovery, reduced time to insight, better data quality management, and enhanced regulatory compliance.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3500 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.2, FORMAT markdown;